  "title": "Fire Officer",
  "description": "<p>We’re Hiring: <strong>Fire Officer</strong></p><p>Work Location:<strong> </strong>Singapore Changi Cargo Complex</p><p><strong>Start Date:</strong> Immediate / Before 15th Feb 2026<br /></p><p><strong>*Job Description: *</strong></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Operate and have to monitor fire control room (FCR) systems in assigned hangars and buildings, including all fire detection and suppression systems as per SOPs.</p><p>Conduct regular fire safety patrols of Airline House and Hangar Complex, inspecting escape routes, firefighting equipment, and hazardous material storage.</p><p>Respond to fire alarm activation's or emergencies and support the on-site incident commander in firefighting and evacuation efforts.</p><p>Serve as fire-watcher during hot work operations; ensure proper permits and safety checks are in place and maintained.</p><p>Report, record, and communicate all fire safety incidents, defects, and operational irregularities to relevant authorities and stakeholders.</p><p>Attend, support, and facilitate fire evacuation drills, fire warden courses, and fire safety training as required.</p><p>Maintain accurate patrol records, incident logbooks, and assist in equipment readiness and maintenance follow-ups.</p><p>Uphold discipline, proper attire, and professional conduct in line with SIA/SIAEC protocols.<br /></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>At least 2 years’ experience as an operational firefighter with SCDF, AES, or Industrial Fire Brigade </p><p>Physically fit and able to respond to fire incidents and emergencies effectively.</p><p>Familiarity with fire alarm and suppression systems in large buildings or aviation environments is highly desirable.</p><p>Good knowledge of Singapore Fire Safety Act, SCDF regulations, and relevant Codes of Practice</p><p>Attentive, reliable, and able to work rotating shifts, including nights, weekends, and public holidays.</p><p>Able to operate inspection tools (e.g. gas detector), tablet computers for reporting, and communication devices.</p><p>Good communication and teamwork skills.</p><p>Additional certifications in fire safety, CERT, or related fields will be advantageous.</p>",
